In the year 1950, the late retired president Daniel Toroitich Arap Moi married the love of his life Lena Moi at the African inland church mission in Eldama Ravine, we traced 85-year-old Lily Settim, who Lena approached to be part of her bridal party and she talks of a wedding that left many talking as the bride wore a wedding gown, unlike other local women who put on a white dress and a white headscarf.